471 class Quaternion
472 {
473 public:
474 union {
475 struct {
479 real r;
480
485 real i;
486
491 real j;
492
497 real k;
498 };
499
503 real data[4];
504 };

507
512 Quaternion() : r(1), i(0), j(0), k(0) {}
513
538 Quaternion(const real r, const real i, const real j, const real k)
539 : r(r), i(i), j(j), k(k)
540 {
541 }
542
547 void normalise()
548 {
549 real d = r*r+i*i+j*j+k*k;
550
551 // Check for zero length quaternion, and use the no-rotation
552 // quaternion in that case.
553 if (d < real_epsilon) {
554 r = 1;
555 return;
556 }
557
558 d = ((real)1.0)/real_sqrt(d);
559 r *= d;
560 i *= d;
561 j *= d;
562 k *= d;
563 }
564
570 void operator *=(const Quaternion &multiplier)
571 {
572 Quaternion q = *this;
573 r = q.r*multiplier.r - q.i*multiplier.i -
574 q.j*multiplier.j - q.k*multiplier.k;
575 i = q.r*multiplier.i + q.i*multiplier.r +
576 q.j*multiplier.k - q.k*multiplier.j;
577 j = q.r*multiplier.j + q.j*multiplier.r +
578 q.k*multiplier.i - q.i*multiplier.k;
579 k = q.r*multiplier.k + q.k*multiplier.r +
580 q.i*multiplier.j - q.j*multiplier.i;
581 }
582
592 void addScaledVector(const Vector3& vector, real scale)
593 {
594 Quaternion q(0,
595 vector.x * scale,
596 vector.y * scale,
597 vector.z * scale);
598 q *= *this;
599 r += q.r * ((real)0.5);
600 i += q.i * ((real)0.5);
601 j += q.j * ((real)0.5);
602 k += q.k * ((real)0.5);
603 }
604
605 void rotateByVector(const Vector3& vector)
606 {
607 Quaternion q(0, vector.x, vector.y, vector.z);
608 (*this) *= q;
609 }
610 };

653 {

664 result.data[6] = (o.data[2]*data[4]) + (o.data[6]*data[5]) + (o.data[10]*data[6]);
665 result.data[10] = (o.data[2]*data[8]) + (o.data[6]*data[9]) + (o.data[10]*data[10]);

843 void setOrientationAndPos(const Quaternion &q, const Vector3 &pos)
844 {
845 data[0] = 1 - (2*q.j*q.j + 2*q.k*q.k);
846 data[1] = 2*q.i*q.j + 2*q.k*q.r;
847 data[2] = 2*q.i*q.k - 2*q.j*q.r;
848 data[3] = pos.x;
849
850 data[4] = 2*q.i*q.j - 2*q.k*q.r;
851 data[5] = 1 - (2*q.i*q.i + 2*q.k*q.k);
852 data[6] = 2*q.j*q.k + 2*q.i*q.r;
853 data[7] = pos.y;
854
855 data[8] = 2*q.i*q.k + 2*q.j*q.r;
856 data[9] = 2*q.j*q.k - 2*q.i*q.r;
857 data[10] = 1 - (2*q.i*q.i + 2*q.j*q.j);
858 data[11] = pos.z;
859 }

1075 void setInverse(const Matrix3 &m)
1076 {
1077 real t4 = m.data[0]*m.data[4];
1078 real t6 = m.data[0]*m.data[5];
1079 real t8 = m.data[1]*m.data[3];
1080 real t10 = m.data[2]*m.data[3];
1081 real t12 = m.data[1]*m.data[6];
1082 real t14 = m.data[2]*m.data[6];
1083
1084 // Calculate the determinant
1085 real t16 = (t4*m.data[8] - t6*m.data[7] - t8*m.data[8]+
1086 t10*m.data[7] + t12*m.data[5] - t14*m.data[4]);
1087
1088 // Make sure the determinant is non-zero.
1089 if (t16 == (real)0.0f) return;
1090 real t17 = 1/t16;
1091
1092 data[0] = (m.data[4]*m.data[8]-m.data[5]*m.data[7])*t17;
1093 data[1] = -(m.data[1]*m.data[8]-m.data[2]*m.data[7])*t17;
1094 data[2] = (m.data[1]*m.data[5]-m.data[2]*m.data[4])*t17;
1095 data[3] = -(m.data[3]*m.data[8]-m.data[5]*m.data[6])*t17;
1096 data[4] = (m.data[0]*m.data[8]-t14)*t17;
1097 data[5] = -(t6-t10)*t17;
1098 data[6] = (m.data[3]*m.data[7]-m.data[4]*m.data[6])*t17;
1099 data[7] = -(m.data[0]*m.data[7]-t12)*t17;
1100 data[8] = (t4-t8)*t17;
1101 }
